  "text": "Kollop disease), suppressor (CD8+) T-cell lymphoma, granulomatous slack skin, peripheral T-cell lymphoma, adult T-cell leukemia/lymphoma, CD30+ large cell lymphoma, and lymphomatoid granulomatosis [CITATION_1] . Evidence from immunophenotyping and T-cell receptor gene rearrangement studies supports the classification of these dermatoses as forms of CTCL [CITATION_2] .",
